cs.NI, cs.CR, cs.DC, cs.SI, cs.CY

This paper discusses the design goals and potential security and privacy issues of future Internet architectures, specifically Content Centric Networking. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also analyzes improvements and new problems, which suggests it could also belong to cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) and cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). The focus on support for mobility and cloud computing could place it in cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Finally, the discussion of privacy concerns could also make it relevant to cs.CY (Computers and Society).
